    "headline": "Iran war 'exposes' strength of U.S. oil production, says investor",
    "summary": "<body><p>STORY: While Krawez believes that a deal to end the conflict between the U.S. and Iran will lower oil prices, he does not \"think they go back to where they were pre-war.\"</p><p>When it comes to oil production, Krawez said the conflict has \"highlighted the value of the Permian [Basin] for the U.S. and really highlighted the strength of the U.S. vis-a-vis Europe and Asia.\"</p><p>\"For that reason,\" he added, \"we actually like companies like Occidental Petroleum that have a lot of domestic production and a lot of domestic supply.\"</p></body>",
